verses.roman:
dāmodara-svarūpa, govinda,-dui jana
mālā-prasāda lañā yāya, yāhāṅ vaiṣṇava-gaṇa

synonyms: dāmodara-svarūpa—Svarūpa Dāmodara; govinda—Govinda; dui jana—two persons; mālā-prasāda—flower garlands and remnants of Lord Jagannātha's food; lañā—taking; yāya—went; yāhāṅ—where; vaiṣṇava-gaṇa—the Vaiṣṇavas.
translation: Svarūpa Dāmodara and Govinda, taking the flower garlands and prasāda of Lord Jagannātha, proceeded to where all the Vaiṣṇavas were standing.
